<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Bestow a Blessing</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">How to bless a person , group , place or thing .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1005" relname="preparation">Figure out exactly who or what the blessing is going to be for .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1005" relname="joint">Using names is always best .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">Think about what attributes</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">you want to create or enhance in the object of the blessing .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1005" relname="joint">Traits such as peace , strength , courage , wit , kindness , grace , good looks , health , happiness , long life , justice , and prosperity are some possibilities .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="10" relname="condition">If you 're religious ,</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="span">look at your scripture for ideas .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1013" relname="span">There might be a verse or quote</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1014" relname="contrast">you want to use ,</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1015" relname="span">or there may be pre-written blessings</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="13" relname="elaboration">you can recite .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1018" relname="contrast">If you 're not religious</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1018" relname="contrast">or do n't want to do a religious-sounding blessing ,</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1017" relname="span">look up some other kinds of quotes , especially poetry .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1016" relname="joint">Even songs .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="span">These can be inspirational</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="19" relname="concession">even if you choose to write your own blessing .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1022" relname="span">Compose the words of the blessing .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1025" relname="contrast">You can write them down</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1025" relname="contrast">or memorize them ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1027" relname="attribution">but make sure</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1027" relname="span">you know what you 're going to say</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="25" relname="circumstance">before you say it .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">Just as with a toast or a speech ,</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1029" relname="span">you do n't want to spoil it</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1030" relname="contrast">by forgetting the words</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1030" relname="contrast">or stumbling .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="span">Keep it concise :</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1034" relname="span">it should n't take more than two minutes</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="32" relname="purpose">to say the whole thing ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1033" relname="joint">and preferably less time than that .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1037" relname="condition">If you want to ,</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="span">you can include a ritual of any sort</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="36" relname="elaboration">you like .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="span">Try reading up on rituals , rites and superstitions</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="38" relname="purpose">to get some ideas .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1041" relname="span">Start with traditions from your own ancestry or ethnicity .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="span">To bless a person ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="elaboration">place your hand on his or her head .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1045" relname="span">Traditionally the right hand ,</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="43" relname="elaboration">which in most people is stronger ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">is the best one</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="purpose">to use .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="48" relname="condition">If touching is unacceptable ,</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="span">hold your hand above the person .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1035" relname="sequence">Recite the blessing .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="span">Have a drink or a special treat</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="contrast">to celebrate ,</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1051" relname="contrast">or give the object of the blessing a gift .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1053" relname="joint">Do n't use the blessing as a lecture .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1057" relname="span">You can also bless a house , a place of business , the food</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1058" relname="span">you eat , or anything</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="elaboration">you make with your hands .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1060" relname="span">Different people have different ideas</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="58" relname="elaboration">of what a blessing actually does ;</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1062" relname="condition">depending on your point of view ,</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1063" relname="span">it 's a request to the higher Power</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="elaboration">to bestow the real gifts ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1064" relname="span">or it 's an expression of your will with the hope</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="63" relname="elaboration">that what you want will become manifest .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1053" relname="joint">Use phrases in the future tense , such as " May you ... "</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="67" relname="concession">A blessing does n't guarantee good things ,</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="span">but it might help .</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1069" relname="span">In some cultures , it 's traditional to bless children</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="68" relname="circumstance">when they reach certain stages of life , or even on a regular basis .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1053" relname="joint">Blessings can be public or private .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1053" relname="joint">You can do it with a large audience or on your own .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1073" relname="span">Invoke the attributes of people</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="72" relname="elaboration">you admire .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1075" relname="span">You can compare the person</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1076" relname="span">you 're blessing to somebody</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="75" relname="elaboration">who is already great .</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1053" relname="joint">Again , keep the words of your blessing short .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1078" relname="span">It 's the thought</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="78" relname="elaboration">that counts .</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1053" relname="joint">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1081" relname="same_unit">Be smart</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1083" relname="circumstance">when you 're composing the blessing ,</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1083" relname="span">and word it</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="1084" relname="span">so that it wo n't offend the person</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="84" relname="elaboration">you 're blessing or somebody watching .</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1086" relname="condition">If in doubt ,</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="1086" relname="span">skip any mention of deities</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="87" relname="elaboration">( God or gods ) .</segment>
